Now a popular series in the country, the ICEA Lion King of The Course, started in 2016 as a Year Opener at Machakos, an idea by Malawi-based Kenyan golfer Kimanzi Muthengi who in 2017 sort sponsorship from ICEA Lion Insurance who in turn saw an opportunity to support and reward their clients in the Eastern region.
This is where the event changed from Year Opener to ICEA King of The Course though it was until last year when more events were added, courtesy of the insurance company. Thus more events were introduced at Ruiru Sports Club, Thika Greens Golf Resort, Nanyuki Sports Club, Nandi Bears and Nyali Golf and Country Club.





However because of Covid-19 pandemic, the Nandi and Nyali legs had to be cancelled until this year. The 2020 Machakos leg was held on January 4, where home player James Ndunda then playing off handicap six carded 37 points in an event played on a tough course then, to become the 2020 King of The Course.
Ndunda is one of the locals drawn for the weekend’s battle with others including past winner Larry Wambua and Railway’s Adelbert Omooria.
Besides the past winners, other Machakos golfers who are also eyeing this year’s title include Victor Mutwii, Ibrahim Lande, John Kitaka, Samuel Theuri, Tito Musyoka, David Mwangangi, Ben Mungata and Collins Kaloki all of whom have been playing well lately. Besides prizes for club members, the sponsors ICEA Lion are also providing a number of other prizes for guests and staff.



