Those going for the guests include include the strong contingent from Royal Nairobi Golf Club led by club captain Sylvester Odhiambo, a line-up that includes Maurice Njue, Hesbon Odumbe, Felix Ochieng and Kenya Golf Union chairman Ben Omuodo who is also a member at Machakos Golf Club.
Because of the big entry, 82 players are drawn in the morning from 6am while 76 players will be battling it out in the afternoon. From Machakos, the next stop-over of the series will be Thika Greens Golf Resort on January 15, with Ruiru staging the third event the following day before action moves to Nanyuki on January 23. The Nandi and Nyali events are scheduled for May 29, and October 30.
Winners of those events will then converge at Machakos Golf Club in January 2022 to determine the all legs King of The course champion. 
Meanwhile Limuru Country Club sets its 2021 agenda with the Directors, and Lady Captain year Opener tournament which is being sponsored by Keroche Breweries and where a field of 150 had by Thursday listed their names to tackle the course.
Vet Lab Sports Club has organised an event where outgoing captain Adam Nyaga will hand over the captainship to the new captain George Kingori. The event has also attracted an impressive field.



